Method
Step 1:
Combine yoghurt, garlic, ginger, lemon juice, oil, spices and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large ceramic bowl. 
Cut 2 slits in top of each chicken thigh, making sure not to cut all the way through. 
Add chicken to yoghurt mixture and turn to coat well. 
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

Step 2: 
Preheat oven to 220Â°C. Grease and line a large baking dish. 
Place chicken in dish and roast for 30 minutes or until cooked through. 
Serve with rice and lemon.
